
Overview of noun wear

The noun wear has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. wear -- (impairment resulting from long use; "the tires showed uneven wear")
2. clothing, article of clothing, vesture, wear, wearable, habiliment -- (a covering designed to be worn on a person's body)
3. wear, wearing -- (the act of having on your person as a covering or adornment; "she bought it for everyday wear")

